The parents of a teenage girl who suffered severe injuries after being dragged down a suburban street by a car say their daughter will have to learn to walk, talk and eat again.

Samantha Giufre, 18, remains in hospital fighting for her life after she was found in a gutter on Myall Road in Casula, south west of Sydney, on September 7.

Ms Giufre was rushed to Liverpool Hospital where she remains in intensive care after suffering multiple fractures to her skull and face, along with bleeding on her brain. 

