'We don't know whether she'll talk, whether she'll see. We don't know how she will end up, knowing that someone has taken that away from her. She's a good kid, she didn't deserve this,' her mother Karen said.

'The image of Samantha when we saw of her in the hospital… I just want to see her like she was originally. She doesn't look like that any more.' 

Doctors believe Samantha may have sustained permanent brain damage and may be blind in one eye following the incident.

